Write typescript application. It will have backend and frontend part. Backend part will serve static markdown files.
Frontend part will use markdown-it to render html pages from the static files. It has to support obsidian links
like [[link to to another page]] and way to use custom plugins for example like obsidan ```plugin ```

What to use
-----------

- For backend use appropriate typescript libraries
- For front-end, do no use rect, vue or similar frameworks. If you use any framework it has to be lightweight.
  Critical priotity is html size of final page. 


